==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncarnate
<hw>Un*car"nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not fleshly;
specifically, not made flesh; not incarnate.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncarnate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uncarnate
<hw>Un*car"nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>carnate</ets>.]</ety> <def>To divest of
flesh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncart</ent>⟦br⟧
